  "executive_profile": {
    "headline": "Executive Profile: Chico Loco 40",
    "story": "Chico Loco 40 operates as the Founder, COO, and CTO at the sole owner of CL40 World LLC and alongside his creative partner LB0025, 'WR Beats'. The artistic journey began in 2011 with the initiation of hip-hop lyricism, heavily influenced by personal hardship and street resilience. This timeline followed the passing of his father, M'Hamed Libari, in 2010 near the Ibis Hotel in Playa, Tangier, whose estate and archives are now fully managed under the artist’s historical legacy project.",
    "detention_and_record": "The artist served a historical detention sentence of 4 years, which was reduced by 3 months following a Royal Pardon by King Mohammed VI, bringing the actual time served to 3 years and 9 months. The adversity, institutional struggles, and survival experienced during this period directly inform the raw authenticity of his professional catalogue and brand identity.",
    "rehabilitation_and_metrics": "Following a complete and successful cessation of substance use, the artist maintains an active psychiatric recovery regimen to support continuous neurological well-being and operational focus. Within a 6-month operational window, the rollout of the Matrics project achieved a verified reach of 134 billion impressions through US-focused distribution and press syndication.",
    "legacy": "Known @ChicoLoco40, he is based in America and driven by the legacy of the 2010 Global Vision 'M'Hamed Libari'. Co-Founder, COO & CTO of CL40 World, he is driving entertainment global entity, music syndicate label operations with legal rights, strategic journalism, PR, digital asset management and global distribution.",
